# 🌱 Carbon Receipt Impact Tracker

A full-stack web application to help businesses measure and reduce their carbon footprint by switching from paper to digital receipts.

---

## 🚀 Features

- 📊 Track CO₂ saved based on digital receipts
- 🧾 Compare digital vs paper usage
- 📈 Monthly impact reports
- 📥 Export CSV report
- ⚙️ RESTful API with Express.js
- 🌐 Dashboard built in React.js
- ☁️ MongoDB for persistent storage

---

## 📁 Project Structure

MS36-CARBON-RECEIPT-MAIN/
│
├── data/                         # Emission factors or static config
│   └── emissionFactors.js
│
├── models/                       # Mongoose schemas for MongoDB
│   ├── Impact.js
│   └── Receipt.js
│
├── routes/                       # All Express route handlers
│   ├── co2Routes.js
│   └── receiptRoutes.js
│
├── src/                          # Frontend React code (if embedded)
│   └── components/
│       └── CarbonImpactDashboard.js
│
├── .env                          # Environment variables (Mongo URI, etc.)
├── .gitignore                   # Git ignore file
├── index.js                     # Main server entry point (Express app)
├── package.json                 # Node.js project config
├── package-lock.json            # NPM lock file
├── seed.js                      # DB seeding script
└── README.md                    # Project documentation


---

## ⚙️ Backend Setup (Node.js + Express)

### 🔧 Prerequisites
- Node.js & npm
- MongoDB (local or Atlas)

### 📦 Install Dependencies
```bash
cd backend
npm install

🔑 Environment Setup
Create a .env file in backend/:

MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/carbon
PORT=5000

▶️ Start Server
npm start
Server will run at: http://localhost:5000

🌐 Frontend Setup (React)
📦 Install Dependencies
cd frontend
npm install

▶️ Run Frontend
npm start
App will run at: http://localhost:3000

🛠️ API Endpoints
| Method | Endpoint                     | Description                          |
| ------ | ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| `POST` | `/calculate-saving`          | Save monthly paper receipt reduction |
| `GET`  | `/report/:businessId`        | Fetch carbon report for business     |
| `GET`  | `/report/:businessId/export` | Download report as CSV               |
| `GET`  | `/co2-saved/:businessId`     | CO₂ saved from digital receipts      |

📊 Dashboard Preview
React Dashboard UI with TailwindCSS

Monthly CO₂ savings table

Export to CSV button

Responsive design

📌 Emission Factors
Configured in: backend/data/emissionFactors.js

module.exports = {
  paperReceipt: { gramsCO2PerReceipt: 2.5 },
  digitalReceipt: { gramsCO2Saved: 4 }
};


